2026-06-09 14:09:56,850 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Starshield: Segment Classification and Revenue Disclosure\n\n### Glossary Definition\nThe S-1 glossary defines **Starshield** as "a secure satellite network designed specifically for government customers and national security applications." It is described as a dedicated network built on Starlink\'s infrastructure, focused on three core mission areas: Earth observation, global secure communications, and hosted payloads, with high-assurance cryptographic capabilities tailored to military and government requirements.\n\n### Reporting Segment\nStarshield revenue is included in the **Connectivity** segment — one of SpaceX\'s three reporting segments (Space, Connectivity, and AI). Within the Connectivity segment, Starshield revenue is categorized under the **Enterprise & Government** revenue line item.\n\n### Revenue Contribution Disclosure\n**No standalone revenue figure is disclosed exclusively for Starshield.** Its revenue is aggregated into the broader "Enterprise & Government" line item, which a footnote clarifies also includes Starlink Mobile service offerings. The Enterprise & Government line item amounts are:\n\n| Year | Enterprise & Government Revenue |\n|------|-------------------------------|\n| 2025 | $4,179 million |\n| 2024 | $2,769 million |\n| 2023 | $1,052 million |\n\nWhile Starshield is not broken out as a separate line item, the MD&A narrative provides incremental growth figures for the broader "government connectivity business" (which encompasses Starshield):\n- **2025:** Government connectivity revenue grew by **$193 million**\n- **2024:** Government connectivity revenue grew by **$1,250 million**\n\n### Revenue Recognition\nThe filing discloses that Starshield revenue is primarily derived from **long-term, fixed-price contracts** with U.S. Government and national security customers, recognized over time using the **cost-to-cost input method**.\n\n### Key Takeaway\nThe filing does not provide sufficient information to isolate Starshield\'s specific revenue contribution. Investors cannot distinguish Starshield revenue from Starlink Mobile or other enterprise/government connectivity revenue within the aggregated Enterprise & Government line item. This absence of granular disclosure is analytically material given Starshield\'s strategic significance to the government business.\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}'})
